               <head>Divan of Shahi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Dīvān by Amīr Shāhī Sabzavārī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n2008042373 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3872-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656938.0x000001 viaf_26536597">Amīr Shāhī Sabzavārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656938.0x000001 viaf_26536597">امير شاهى سبزوارى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20641">Dīvān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20641">ديوان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Highly refined de luxe manuscript, consisting of a limited collection of ghazals, rubāʿīs, and smaller compositions</p>
                        <p>Illuminated with ʿunvān, ornamental panels separating poems, rulings, and large gold flecking or zar afshānī in borders and flyleaves, and a fine spray on paper in text areas; panel of a stylised scene of animals around a tree in gold, after colophon (f. 37r); calligraphic nastaʿlīq-i khafī</p>
                        <p>Colophon (f. 37r) date: avākhir of Rabīʿ II 912 (1506) </p>
                        <p>Scribe: ʿAlī al-Kātib</p>
                        <p>Ownership seals and inscriptions, several obliterated</p>
                        <p>Loose red velvet cover over binding</p>
                        <p>Text block detatched from binding</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
